description: For sale: $349,900. Welcome to a restored craftsman bungalow at a price considerably less than today's replacement cost w/ over 3,400 square feet, 5 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms & great storage. Gorgeous original baseboards, moldings, custom birch radiator covers & hardwood floors throughout the main level adds a ton of character & warmth. Natural light throughout including the sunroom & finished lower level walkout w/ its in-floor heating. Originally fieldstone with newer stucco exterior. Updated windows, plumbing, electrical, heating & cooling. Easy single level living on the main floor that features a master suite, 2 more bedrooms & bath w/ claw foot tub, laundry room, updated kitchen, walk-in pantry & beautiful Birdseye maple floors & cabinets. Open floor plan accommodates large gatherings w/ the serving area flowing into a great room, formerly "Auhll's Bakery" w/ 9 foot ceilings & 13 windows & a spacious deck. Double lot w/ mature trees on a quiet street close to parks and trails.

For sale: $333,945. Enjoy the convenience of association-maintained living with this 2,085 square foot, three-bedroom, two-and-a-half bath floorplan. This lovely townhome has a two-car garage that leads into the spacious lower-level entryway. Finish this space to add an additional bedroom with a private bathroom, or recreation room. Mirroring the style and touches of the single family and villa collection, this townhome features beautiful stone accents and charming brackets at the peak of the roof line, common of the Craftsman style. This townhome is also in one of the metro area's newest communities, Gateway at McKnight. If you enjoy being close to the city lifestyle, without the hustle and bustle, this is the home for you. This open-concept floorplan offers plenty of additional living space throughout, beginning on the main level. Enjoy this gorgeous open layout between the kitchen, dining area, and family room. The Prescott's kitchen offers a large center island with space for additional seating, a shelved pantry, and stainless steel appliances. Off the kitchen lies a lovely balcony for outdoor seating and relaxation. A lovely feature of this floorplan is that the main level also offers a private flex room, perfect for those needing a multi-purpose room or home office. Upstairs, you'll find all three bedrooms and a laundry room. The main hallway bathroom offers an option to add a double-bowl vanity as well. You'll love the private owner's suite which showcases a lovely decora...

description: For sale: $225,000. CUTE AS A BUTTON! This beautiful home on an oversized lot is only available due to relocation. Nestled on a picturesque tree lined street near parks, schools, dining, and shopping- and minutes from St. Paul or Minneapolis. This home has always been meticulously maintained inside and out, with a virtually maintenance free exterior, and original woodwork and hardwood floors. There are sunny light filled living spaces on the main floor, and two generous sized bedrooms (one of them has access to the rear deck) and lovely tiled main floor bath. Upstairs you will find a very generous space that provides opportunity for a master, 3rd bedroom, or den/office. Downstairs there is a nice finished area with additional opportunities to make it your own and add equity. Also be sure to check out the large backyard with firepit and oversized insulated garage with work/storage space(that can be converted into a two car) and carport in the rear.

description: For sale: $675,000. LAKE LIVING at its finest with the convenience of the Twin Cities! Enjoy 85 ft of lake shore, beautiful views & recreational activities on Lake Gervais in this pristine home that boasts many updates. Large kitchen with walk-in pantry & island, family room with built-in cherry cabinets, gas fireplace and huge windows to let in southern exposure & lake views; plus grand formal living room/dining room. Upper level offers quality new carpet and 4 large BRs including master suite with balcony overlooking the lake and a lovely updated bath with double sinks, custom cabinetry, and brand new tiled shower. Re-landscaped lakefront, new AC units, and almost all newer Pella windows. Workshop off garage and crawlspace provides extra storage. Paver driveway wraps around side of the house providing ample space for boat/RV parking. Cement pad next to deck would be perfect for a hot tub! Enjoy life on the lake on the new paver patio on the waterfront and flower gardens for relaxing, beautiful summers.
